I don't think we need a whole queue here; a single deferred will do.

For example, we could replace `requestQueue` with `nextLoopDeferred: undefined | IDeferred<void>`. 


```suggestion
    public doProcessOutgoingRequests(): Promise<void> {
        if (!this.isTaskRunning) {
            // The loop is not yet running. kick it off.
            await this.executeTask();
            return;
        }
     
        // The loop is already running, but we need to do another loop. Blah blah avoid race.   
        // Ensure that nextLoopDeferred is set, which tells `executeTask` to do another loop.
        if (!this.nextLoopDeferred) {
            this.nextLoopDeferred = defer();
        }
        
        await this.nextLoopDeferred.promise();
    }        
```

... and then in executeTask, replace the access to `requestQueue` with:

```typescript
let d = this.nextLoopDeferred;
this.nextLoopDeferred = undefined;
// ... loop
d.resolve();
```

